Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All parameters are within normal limits except for elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and borderline high triglycerides. Liver function, electrolytes, glucose, and protein levels are normal. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and monitoring of lipid profile.
